-- S. Korea to Spend $1.7 Billion to Develop Alternative Energy, Daily Says
-- Sungwoo Park
-- 2010-06-28T22:15:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/s-korea-to-spend-1-7-billion-to-develop-alternative-energy-daily-says.html

          
          
             South Korea plans to spend 2 trilli
on won ($1.7 billion) by 2015 to help develop parts and
equipment for alternative energy industries such as solar and
wind power generation and fuel cells, the Seoul Economic
Daily reported, citing unidentified officials in the government
and related industries.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Sungwoo Park in Seoul at 
 spark47@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        